# =================================================================
# .gitignore  —  what Git should NEVER track
# -----------------------------------------------------------------
# The golden rule for this project: large CAD/FEA source files do NOT
# live in this repository. They go to GitHub Releases or Cloudflare R2,
# and the site links to them by URL (see the README). The patterns
# below are a safety net so a giant file can't be committed by accident.
# =================================================================

# ---- Large engineering source files (host these externally!) ----
*.SLDPRT
*.SLDASM
*.SLDDRW
*.sldprt
*.sldasm
*.slddrw
*.step
*.stp
*.iges
*.igs
*.x_t
*.x_b
*.prt
*.asm
*.catpart
*.catproduct

# ---- Ansys / simulation archives & junk ----
*.wbpz
*.wbpj
*_files/
*.mechdat
*.mechdb
*.cdb
*.rst
*.rth
*.db
*.dbb
*.err
*.out

# ---- Big media that should be optimised/hosted elsewhere ----
*.zip
*.rar
*.7z
*.mp4
*.mov

# ---- iCloud / OS / editor cruft ----
.DS_Store
.AppleDouble
Icon?
*.icloud
Thumbs.db
ehthumbs.db
desktop.ini
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*~

# ---- Node (only if you ever add build tooling; not needed now) ----
node_modules/
npm-debug.log*

# ---- Claude Code personal/local settings (don't publish these) ----
.claude/settings.local.json

# -----------------------------------------------------------------
# NOTE: small files that SHOULD be tracked and are intentionally NOT
# ignored: your optimised images in assets/img/, the resume PDF in
# assets/resume/, the favicon, and all HTML/CSS/JS/JSON.
# If you ever need to keep a sample model in the repo for the 3D viewer,
# use a small .glb and force-add it:  git add -f assets/models/demo.glb
# =================================================================
